                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="anglocatholicism_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a movement within the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-church-of-england" title="Church of England definition"><span class="ndv">Church of England</span></a> that emphasizes its connections with the Roman Catholic Church. <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/anglo-catholic_1#anglo_catholic_topg_1" title="Anglo-Catholic definition"><span class="ndv">Anglo-Catholic</span></a> ideas were strongly expressed in the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-oxford-movement#the_oxford_movement_topg_1" title="Oxford Movement definition"><span class="ndv">Oxford Movement</span></a> of the 1830s. When the Church of England started to accept women as priests in the 1990s some Anglo-Catholic priests who were opposed to this joined the Roman Catholic Church.</span></span> <span class="xrefs" hclass="xrefs" xt="see" htag="span"><span class="prefix">see also</span> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-ordination-of-women" title="ordination of women definition"><span class="xr-g" href="theordinationofwomen_ge"><span class="xh">ordination of women</span></span></a></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
